# frontend-portfolio — Project Context

## Stack
- **Framework:** Nuxt 4 (App Router, `pages/`, `layouts/`, `server/`)
- **UI:** Vue 3 Composition API (`<script setup>` only — no Options API)
- **Styling:** SCSS (never plain CSS) — use variables from `assets/styles/_variables.scss`
- **State:** Pinia (no Vuex)
- **HTTP:** `$fetch` / `useFetch` (no Axios)
- **Types:** TypeScript strict mode — all props, composables, and API responses must be typed
- **Package manager:** pnpm

## Project Structure
```
assets/
  styles/
    _variables.scss     ← SCSS tokens (colors, spacing, fonts)
    _mixins.scss
    main.scss
components/
  ui/                   ← Generic reusable (Button, Card, Badge…)
  sections/             ← Page sections (Hero, Projects, About, Contact…)
composables/            ← Prefixed use* (e.g. useProjects.ts)
pages/
  index.vue
  projects/
    [slug].vue
server/
  api/                  ← Nitro endpoints if needed
public/
  images/
types/                  ← Shared TS interfaces/types
```

## Conventions
- Components: PascalCase filenames, `<script setup lang="ts">` at top
- Composables: `use` prefix, return typed refs/computed
- SCSS: BEM naming for custom classes; Vuetify utility classes preferred over custom where possible
- No `any` types — use `unknown` + type guards if needed
- Prefer `const` over `let`; never `var`
- Async data: always use `useFetch`/`useAsyncData` — never raw `fetch` in components

## Git
- Default branch: `main`
- Feature branches: `feat/description`, bugs: `fix/description`
- Commit format: `feat(scope): message` / `fix(scope): message` / `chore(scope): message`
- Never commit directly to `main`
- PRs should target `main` from a feature branch
